Changelog

All notable changes to ScreenSafe will be documented in this section.

Added

* Planned support for scheduled break reminders.
* Planned expansion of usage history beyond the current summary view.
* Planned enhancement of charting and data visualization for daily and weekly reports.

Changed

* Future updates are expected to refine the user interface and improve navigation flow as development continues.

[1.0.0] - Current Version

Added

* Finalized the six main screens shown in the wireframe:

  * Welcome Screen
  * Dashboard or Home Screen
  * Set Limit Screen
  * Warning or Alert Screen
  * Daily or Weekly Summary Screen
  * Settings Screen
* Added a clearer user flow from the Welcome Screen to the Dashboard and then to Summary, Settings, Warning, and Set Limit.
* Added local settings storage for user preferences.
* Added reminder frequency selection.
* Added weekly summary tracking.
* Added theme selection in Settings.
* Added warning-flow logic for daily screen time limits.
* Added basic Android screen-time tracking through UsageStatsManager.

Changed

* Expanded the original project concept into a more complete wireframe-based design.
* Refined the dashboard to include progress display and quick actions such as Set Limit, View Report, and Take a Break.
* Refined the settings design to include notification controls, reminder settings, daily summary settings, theme selection, reset options, and save options.

Fixed

* Improved the connection between the project outline, wireframe, and code plan so that all parts now align more clearly.

[0.1.0] - Previous Version

Added

* Initial app concept for ScreenSafe as an Android app focused on monitoring screen time.
* Initial outline describing the business problem of excessive screen time.
* Initial plan for core features such as usage limits, warnings, summaries, and settings.

Changed

* Established the first version of the project structure and general screen ideas before the wireframe and code stages.

Fixed

* Clarified the project goal so the app remained focused on digital wellness and healthier device habits.
